{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":14545,"record_hash":"sha256:17cc2ee99d0efbb082a6012fab4e64f214ca76cf0b985c006e977f2c4f623bb0","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:56:34.910Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Delete File: [REDACTED:entropy].md\n*** Add File: [REDACTED:entropy].md\n+# Capture Workflow\n+\n+This document parks future discovery and hook behavior. The current explicit-path\n+POC workflow is defined in [First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md).\n+\n+## Current Boundary\n+\n+The POC command requires an explicit transcript path:\n+\n+```text\n+but agentlog capture --agent <codex|claude> --transcript-path <path>\n+```\n+\n+It should not infer the current session, scan the machine, serialize GitMeta, or\n+guess branch ownership. Transcript `cwd` is validation-only and must not select\n+the repository.\n+\n+## Future Inputs\n+\n+Later capture can accept increasingly implicit inputs, in this order of\n+preference:\n+\n+1. exact transcript path from a hook payload\n+2. explicit provider session id\n+3. agent-provided environment session id\n+4. recent files in known agent directories, filtered by repository cwd\n+\n+The command should prefer no capture over capturing a plausible but unrelated\n+session.\n+\n+## Codex Discovery\n+\n+Do not implement discovery in the first POC.\n+\n+When added, resolve the Codex home directory as:\n+\n+1. `CODEX_HOME`, when set\n+2. otherwise the user's home directory joined with `.codex`\n+\n+On macOS and Linux this normally means `~/.codex`. On native Windows, use the\n+Windows user profile home directory, for example `%USERPROFILE%\\.codex`. Under\n+WSL, use the Linux home directory and `~/.codex`.\n+\n+Codex CLI session JSONL files have been observed under:\n+\n+```text\n+$[REDACTED:entropy]*.jsonl\n+```\n+\n+`session_index.jsonl` may exist next to the session tree, but the first\n+discovery implementation should prefer JSONL transcript files because they are\n+the same artifact the explicit-path capture already parses. Do not depend on\n+Codex desktop SQLite state in the first discovery pass.\n+\n+Discovery should:\n+\n+- scan a small recent window first, sorted by modification time descending\n+- inspect only enough early JSONL records to find session metadata and cwd\n+- canonicalize candidate cwd values and require them to be the selected\n+  GitButler worktree root or inside it\n+- auto-select only when exactly one candidate matches\n+- ask for `--transcript-path` when no candidate or several candidates match\n+\n+## Claude Discovery\n+\n+Do not implement discovery in the first POC.\n+\n+When added, resolve the Claude config directory as:\n+\n+1. `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR`, when set\n+2. otherwise the user's home directory joined with `.claude`\n+\n+Then look under:\n+\n+```text\n+<claude-config-dir>/projects/<encoded-cwd>/*.jsonl\n+```\n+\n+The encoded cwd is lossy, so use it only to narrow the search. Validate cwd\n+fields inside JSONL records before selecting a candidate.\n+\n+## Freshness\n+\n+When no exact transcript path is provided, freshness should consider:\n+\n+- file modification time\n+- session metadata timestamp\n+- matching repository cwd\n+- matching session id from an environment variable or hook payload\n+- a configurable maximum age\n+\n+## Hook Usage\n+\n+Hook usage is the next milestone after explicit-path capture works. Prefer hook\n+payloads that include the exact transcript path:\n+\n+```text\n+but -C \"$REPO\" agentlog capture \\\n+  --agent codex \\\n+  --transcript-path \"$TRANSCRIPT_PATH\"\n+```\n+\n+Session-id hooks can come later:\n+\n+```text\n+but -C \"$REPO\" agentlog capture \\\n+  --agent codex \\\n+  --session-id \"$CODEX_THREAD_ID\"\n+```\n+\n+Do not implement hook lifecycle machinery in the POC. When hooks are added,\n+normalize only the events needed by the first hook integration. Include an\n+adapter-specific transcript preparation step only if the agent writes transcripts\n+asynchronously.\n+\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:56:34.910Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}